[1] Cholera - Niger (Tilabery)
Date: Wed, 2 June 2004
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO Outbreak Report [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2004_06_02/en/>

Cholera in Niger
----------------
The Ministry of Health, Niger has reported a total of 137 cases
including 5 deaths from cholera between 3 May 2004 and 17 May 2004 in
the region of Tillabery (City of Ayorou).
_Vibrio cholerae_ O1 El Tor Ogawa has been laboratory-confirmed. This
outbreak is linked to heavy rainfalls in the area, and to population
movements along the Niger River for trade purposes, between Gao and
Timbuctu Provinces in Mali and Tillabery district in Niger.
The Ministry of Health, with the support of WHO is implementing
control measures in the area, including the restriction of
marketplaces and health education activities around safe drinking
water.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
