[2] Cholera - Uganda (Kayunga)
Date: Sat, 29 May 2004
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhuanet.com [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2004-05/29/content_1497396.htm>

Cholera killed 7 people recently in Kayunga district, about 100 km
from Kampala, bringing to 24 the total number of people died of the
disease since it broke out in Uganda in February 2004, the New Vision
newspaper reported Sat, 29 May 2004.
It quoted Kayunga hospital medical superintendent Ahmed Matovu as
saying that 3 died last week in the hospital and 4 others died in
their homes. Matovu said the Ugandan Health Ministry has sent health
workers to the area to contain the situation and the district has set
up a camp to accommodate cholera suspects.
In the country's northwestern district of Nebbi, 12 people have died
out of the 258 cases since February 2004 and the disease has also
killed 5 in Kampala since the epidemic broke out.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
