[3] Diarrhea - Nepal (Siraha)
Date: Sat, 29 May 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: Nepal News [edited]
<http://www.nepalnews.com.np/archive/2004/may/arc_may04_29.htm>

Diarrhea kills 9 in Siraha
--------------------------
The spread of diarrhea in the villages of Siraha district has killed
9 people and infected hundreds of others. Serious victims have been
rushed for treatment to the district hospital, according to Nepal
Samacharpatra.
Dr Raj Kumar Chaudhari, chief at the District Public Health Office
said that 2 people have died in the district health office. He added
that health teams have been deployed to several of the affected areas
in the district.
Similarly, diarrhea is spreading in the Sindhuli district as well.
Over 2 dozen patients have been rushed to local health posts and a
child in Belghari has died. 2 schools in the area have been closed in
an effort to slow down the epidemic.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
